HEADWORD: Charadriiformes
<hw>Charadriiformes</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>large diverse order of
aquatic birds found along seacoasts and inland waters; shorebirds and
coastal diving birds; most feed on animal life.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order <ord>Charadriiformes</ord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

